================================================================================
                         PREAMBLE AND RECITALS
================================================================================

WHEREAS, the Licensor has developed certain software known as "Perlthon," which
enables the importation and execution of Perl programming language modules from
within the Python programming language runtime environment through the
intermediary mechanism of a Rust-based extension module employing the PyO3
foreign function interface framework and a supplementary C language glue layer
interfacing with the Perl interpreter embedding application programming
interface; and

WHEREAS, the Licensor desires to make the Software available to the general
public under terms that are maximally permissive with respect to copying,
modification, redistribution, sublicensing, relicensing, and commercial
exploitation; and

WHEREAS, the Licensor simultaneously and with equal force desires to ensure that
under no circumstances whatsoever shall the Software, or any derivative,
modification, fork, port, translation, adaptation, or transformation thereof, be
deployed, utilized, executed, instantiated, or otherwise operated in any
production environment, as that term is defined herein; and

WHEREAS, the Licensor recognizes and acknowledges that the very concept of
embedding a Perl interpreter within a Python runtime for the purpose of calling
Perl modules from Python code represents a sufficiently extraordinary
architectural decision that the restriction of production use is not merely
advisable but constitutes a moral imperative;

NOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the mutual covenants, agreements,
representations, and warranties contained herein, and for other good and
valuable consideration, the receipt and sufficiency of which are hereby
acknowledged, the Licensor grants to any person obtaining a copy of this
Software and associated documentation files (collectively, the "Software") the
following rights, privileges, and licenses, subject to the terms, conditions,
restrictions, limitations, and obligations set forth in this License Agreement
(the "Agreement" or "License"):

