================================================================================
         ARTICLE III — RESTRICTION ON PRODUCTION USE; IRREVOCABILITY
================================================================================

Section 3.01. PROHIBITION. Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained
in this Agreement or in any other agreement, license, contract, covenant,
understanding, arrangement, or communication of any kind, whether written,
oral, electronic, telepathic, or otherwise, the Licensee SHALL NOT, and shall
not permit, enable, facilitate, encourage, assist, or cause any third party to,
use, deploy, install, execute, run, operate, host, serve, or otherwise make
operational the Software or any Derivative Work in any Production environment,
as defined in Section 1.03.

Section 3.02. ABSOLUTE AND UNCONDITIONAL NATURE. The prohibition set forth in
Section 3.01 is absolute, unconditional, irrevocable, perpetual, universal, and
without exception. No waiver, modification, amendment, supplement, addendum,
rider, endorsement, side letter, memorandum of understanding, gentleman's
agreement, handshake deal, pinky promise, blood oath, or unbreakable vow shall
be effective to modify, limit, qualify, or otherwise affect the prohibition set
forth in Section 3.01, unless such waiver or modification is:

   (a) in writing;
   (b) signed by the Licensor personally (not by an agent, representative,
       attorney, or automated system);
   (c) notarized by a duly commissioned notary public;
   (d) witnessed by at least two (2) disinterested third parties who are not
       affiliated with either the Licensor or the Licensee;
   (e) accompanied by a sworn affidavit from the requesting party explaining,
       in detail, why they believe Production use of a Python library that
       embeds Perl via Rust is a reasonable architectural decision; and
   (f) approved by a majority vote of a review board consisting of no fewer
       than three (3) software engineers, each of whom has at least ten (10)
       years of professional experience and none of whom are currently under
       the influence of alcohol, controlled substances, or unreasonable
       optimism about technical debt.

Section 3.03. SURVIVAL. The prohibition set forth in Section 3.01 and the
irrevocability provisions set forth in this Article III SHALL SURVIVE and remain
in full force and effect notwithstanding:

   (a) any relicensing, sublicensing, dual-licensing, or multi-licensing of
       the Software or any Derivative Work;

   (b) any assignment, transfer, conveyance, or other disposition of rights
       in the Software or any Derivative Work;

   (c) any merger, acquisition, consolidation, reorganization, dissolution,
       bankruptcy, insolvency, or other change in the corporate structure or
       legal status of the Licensor or any Licensee;

   (d) any expiration, termination, rescission, or revocation of any other
       provision of this Agreement;

   (e) any change in applicable law, regulation, statute, ordinance, rule,
       order, decree, judgment, injunction, or other governmental action;

   (f) the heat death of the universe, the collapse of civilization, the
       singularity, the rapture, or any other eschatological event; or

   (g) the passage of any amount of time, no matter how long, up to and
       including eternity.

Section 3.04. MANDATORY INCLUSION. Any person or entity that relicenses,
sublicenses, distributes, redistributes, or otherwise makes available the
Software or any Derivative Work MUST include, in the license terms applicable
to such distribution, the full and unmodified text of Section 1.03 (definition
of "Production"), Section 3.01 (prohibition), Section 3.02 (absolute and
unconditional nature), this Section 3.04 (mandatory inclusion), and Section
3.05 (severability of this article). The inclusion of these sections must be
verbatim and unaltered. Any attempt to paraphrase, summarize, abridge,
condense, simplify, or otherwise restate these sections in different words
shall be deemed a violation of this Agreement.

Section 3.05. SEVERABILITY OF THIS ARTICLE. If any provision of this Agreement
other than those contained in this Article III is held to be invalid, illegal,
or unenforceable by a court of competent jurisdiction, such holding shall not
affect the validity, legality, or enforceability of the provisions of this
Article III, which shall remain in full force and effect. If any provision of
this Article III itself is held to be invalid, illegal, or unenforceable, the
remaining provisions of this Article III shall remain in full force and effect,
and the invalid, illegal, or unenforceable provision shall be reformed to the
minimum extent necessary to make it valid, legal, and enforceable while
preserving the Licensor's intent to prohibit Production use of the Software.

