              ARTICLE VII — GENERAL PROVISIONS
================================================================================

Section 7.01. ENTIRE AGREEMENT. This Agreement constitutes the entire agreement
between the Licensor and the Licensee with respect to the Software and
supersedes all prior and contemporaneous agreements, understandings,
negotiations, discussions, representations, warranties, and communications,
whether written, oral, electronic, or telepathic, relating to the subject
matter hereof.

Section 7.02. SEVERABILITY. If any provision of this Agreement (other than
those specified in Section 3.05) is held to be invalid, illegal, or
unenforceable by a court of competent jurisdiction, such provision shall be
reformed to the minimum extent necessary to make it valid, legal, and
enforceable, and the remaining provisions of this Agreement shall remain in
full force and effect.

Section 7.03. WAIVER. No failure or delay by the Licensor in exercising any
right, power, or privilege under this Agreement shall operate as a waiver
thereof, nor shall any single or partial exercise of any right, power, or
privilege preclude any other or further exercise thereof or the exercise of
any other right, power, or privilege. The Licensor's decision not to enforce
the no-production-use restriction against one Licensee shall not constitute
a waiver of the Licensor's right to enforce it against any other Licensee,
although the Licensor acknowledges that enforcement presupposes detection,
and detection presupposes that someone would actually admit to deploying
this in production.

Section 7.04. ASSIGNMENT. The Licensee may freely assign, transfer, delegate,
or otherwise dispose of their rights and obligations under this Agreement
without the prior written consent of the Licensor, provided that the assignee
agrees to be bound by the terms of this Agreement, including and especially
Article III.

Section 7.05. GOVERNING LAW. This Agreement shall be governed by and construed
in accordance with the laws of whichever jurisdiction would find the prohibition
on production use most enforceable, without regard to conflicts of law
principles that might lead to the application of the laws of any other
jurisdiction.

Section 7.06. DISPUTE RESOLUTION. Any dispute arising out of or relating to
this Agreement shall be resolved by the parties through good-faith negotiation,
mediation, interpretive dance, or, as a last resort, binding arbitration
conducted in accordance with the rules of a mutually agreed-upon arbitration
body. The prevailing party shall be entitled to recover its reasonable
attorneys' fees and costs.

Section 7.07. NOTICES. All notices, requests, demands, and other communications
required or permitted under this Agreement shall be in writing and shall be
deemed to have been duly given when delivered personally, sent by certified
mail (return receipt requested), sent by reputable overnight courier service,
transmitted by electronic mail with confirmed receipt, or published as a
comment on the relevant GitHub issue.

Section 7.08. HEADINGS. The headings and section titles in this Agreement are
for convenience of reference only and shall not affect the interpretation or
construction of any provision hereof, although the Licensor has endeavored to
make them as entertaining as the subject matter permits.

Section 7.09. COUNTERPARTS. This Agreement may be executed in any number of
counterparts, each of which shall be deemed an original, and all of which
together shall constitute one and the same instrument. The Licensor
acknowledges that in practice this Agreement is "executed" by the act of
downloading, cloning, or forking the Software, which is somewhat less formal
than the traditional exchange of signed documents but is consistent with
prevailing customs in the open source software community.

Section 7.10. NO THIRD-PARTY BENEFICIARIES. This Agreement is intended for the
benefit of the Licensor and the Licensee only and does not confer any rights,
benefits, privileges, or remedies on any third party, except that any person
who suffers damages as a result of the Software being deployed in Production
may invoke Article III in support of their claim against the party responsible
for such deployment.

Section 7.11. FORCE MAJEURE. Neither party shall be liable for any failure or
delay in the performance of its obligations under this Agreement (other than
the obligation not to use the Software in Production, which admits of no
excuse) to the extent that such failure or delay results from acts of God,
war, terrorism, civil unrest, pandemic, epidemic, natural disaster, power
failure, network outage, solar flare, asteroid impact, zombie apocalypse,
robot uprising, kaiju attack, or any other event beyond the reasonable control
of the affected party.

Section 7.12. CONSTRUCTION. This Agreement shall be construed without regard
to any presumption or rule requiring construction against the party causing
this Agreement to be drafted. Both parties acknowledge that they have had the
opportunity to review this Agreement, or at least to scroll past it, which
amounts to the same thing.

================================================================================
        ARTICLE VIII — COMPLIANCE MONITORING AND ATTESTATION
================================================================================

Section 8.01. COMPLIANCE PROGRAM. The Licensee shall establish, maintain, and
operate a comprehensive compliance program reasonably designed to ensure
adherence to the terms, conditions, and obligations set forth in this Agreement.
Such compliance program shall include, at a minimum, written policies and
procedures, periodic internal assessments, designated compliance personnel,
training curricula, escalation pathways, and remediation protocols. The scope,
scale, and sophistication of the compliance program shall be commensurate with
the Licensee's size, complexity, risk profile, and organizational appetite for
bureaucracy.

Section 8.02. ANNUAL ATTESTATION. The Licensee shall, on or before the
anniversary of the date on which the Licensee first obtained the Software,
and annually thereafter, conduct a self-assessment of their compliance with
this Agreement. The self-assessment shall be documented in a written report
(the "Compliance Report") which shall include:

   (a) a description of the Licensee's use of the Software during the
       preceding twelve (12) month period;

   (b) a certification that the Licensee has not used the Software in
       Production, or a detailed description of any instances in which the
       Licensee may have inadvertently approached Production use, together
       with a description of the corrective actions taken;

   (c) an assessment of the Licensee's compliance program, including any
       identified deficiencies, gaps, weaknesses, or areas for improvement;

   (d) a statement of the Licensee's intentions with respect to the Software
       for the upcoming twelve (12) month period; and

   (e) any other information the Licensee deems relevant, interesting, or
       cathartic.

Section 8.03. RETENTION. The Licensee shall retain the Compliance Report and
all supporting documentation for a period of no less than seven (7) years from
the date of creation, or such longer period as may be required by applicable
law, regulation, or the Licensee's own record retention policy, whichever is
longest. The Licensor shall have no obligation to request, review, read, skim,
glance at, or otherwise acknowledge the existence of any Compliance Report.

Section 8.04. SEVERABILITY OF THIS ARTICLE. This Article VIII is included for
the purpose of establishing a framework for compliance monitoring and does not
create any substantive rights or obligations beyond those already set forth
elsewhere in this Agreement. If this entire Article is deemed invalid, illegal,
unenforceable, unnecessary, excessive, performative, or simply too much, it
may be severed from this Agreement without affecting the validity or
enforceability of any other provision.

