           ARTICLE XIV — INSURANCE AND INDEMNIFICATION
================================================================================

Section 14.01. INSURANCE. The Licensor does not require the Licensee to obtain
or maintain any insurance coverage in connection with the Licensee's use of the
Software. However, the Licensor notes that professional liability insurance,
errors and omissions insurance, cyber liability insurance, technology errors
and omissions insurance, media liability insurance, and general commercial
liability insurance are all widely available in the marketplace, and the
Licensee may wish to consult with a qualified insurance broker regarding the
appropriateness of such coverage in light of the Licensee's particular
circumstances and risk tolerance.

Section 14.02. MUTUAL INDEMNIFICATION. Each party (the "Indemnifying Party")
shall indemnify, defend, and hold harmless the other party and its officers,
directors, employees, agents, successors, and assigns (collectively, the
"Indemnified Parties") from and against any and all claims, demands, actions,
suits, proceedings, losses, damages, liabilities, costs, and expenses
(including reasonable attorneys' fees and court costs) arising out of or
relating to:

   (a) the Indemnifying Party's breach of any representation, warranty,
       covenant, or obligation under this Agreement;

   (b) the Indemnifying Party's negligence, willful misconduct, or intentional
       wrongdoing in connection with the Software; or

   (c) any third-party claim alleging that the Indemnifying Party's use of the
       Software infringes, misappropriates, or otherwise violates the
       intellectual property rights of such third party.

Section 14.03. INDEMNIFICATION PROCEDURES. The Indemnified Party shall promptly
notify the Indemnifying Party of any claim for which indemnification is sought,
shall cooperate with the Indemnifying Party in the defense of such claim, and
shall not settle or compromise any such claim without the Indemnifying Party's
prior written consent. The Indemnifying Party shall have the right to control
the defense of any such claim, provided that the Indemnified Party shall have
the right to participate in the defense at its own expense. The parties
acknowledge that the practical likelihood of any indemnification obligation
arising under this Section is vanishingly small, given the nature of the
Software and the restriction on Production use.

Section 14.04. SEVERABILITY OF THIS ARTICLE. This Article XIV is included for
the purpose of addressing insurance and indemnification matters. In light of
the disclaimer of warranties in Article V and the limitation of liability in
Article VI, the practical effect of this Article may be negligible. If this
entire Article is deemed invalid, illegal, unenforceable, internally
contradictory, or redundant in light of other provisions of this Agreement,
it may be severed from this Agreement without affecting the validity or
enforceability of any other provision.

