           ARTICLE XV — SUCCESSION AND CONTINUITY PLANNING
================================================================================

Section 15.01. CONTINUITY OF LICENSE. In the event that the Licensor becomes
permanently unable or unwilling to exercise the rights, discharge the
obligations, or fulfill the responsibilities of the Licensor under this
Agreement, whether due to death, incapacity, disappearance, extended absence,
loss of interest, pivot to a different technology stack, spiritual awakening,
or any other reason, the rights granted to all Licensees under this Agreement
shall continue in full force and effect in perpetuity, subject to the
continuing applicability of Article III.

Section 15.02. SUCCESSOR LICENSOR. The Licensor may designate a successor
Licensor by written instrument filed with the project repository, published
on the project website, or communicated through any other means reasonably
calculated to provide notice to affected Licensees. Any successor Licensor
shall be bound by all terms of this Agreement and shall not have the power to
modify, amend, or waive any provision of Article III except in accordance with
the procedures set forth in Section 3.02.

Section 15.03. ORPHAN SOFTWARE. In the event that the Software becomes "orphan
software" — that is, software with no active maintainer, no designated
successor Licensor, and no community of contributors willing to assume
responsibility for its ongoing development and maintenance — the rights
granted under this Agreement shall nevertheless continue in full force and
effect, and the prohibition on Production use shall remain binding upon all
Licensees and their successors and assigns. The orphan status of the Software
shall not be construed as an implied waiver of the Production use restriction,
no matter how tempting it may be to reason that "nobody is maintaining it
anyway, so what's the harm."

Section 15.04. SEVERABILITY OF THIS ARTICLE. This Article XV is included for
the purpose of addressing succession and continuity planning. It does not
create any enforceable right to continued maintenance, support, updates, or
development of the Software. If this entire Article is deemed invalid, illegal,
unenforceable, premature, or morbid, it may be severed from this Agreement
without affecting the validity or enforceability of any other provision.

================================================================================
       ARTICLE XVI — DISPUTE ESCALATION AND ALTERNATIVE RESOLUTION
================================================================================

Section 16.01. ESCALATION LADDER. Prior to initiating any formal dispute
resolution proceeding under this Agreement, the parties shall attempt to
resolve any dispute, controversy, or claim through the following escalation
ladder, each step of which shall be attempted in good faith for a period of
not less than fifteen (15) business days before proceeding to the next:

   (a) INFORMAL DISCUSSION. The parties' respective designated representatives
       shall engage in informal, unstructured discussions aimed at identifying
       the nature and scope of the dispute and exploring potential resolutions.
       Such discussions may be conducted in person, by telephone, by video
       conference, by electronic mail, by text message, by carrier pigeon, or
       by any other means of communication mutually agreeable to the parties;

   (b) STRUCTURED NEGOTIATION. If informal discussion fails to resolve the
       dispute, the parties shall engage in structured negotiation, in which
       each party prepares and exchanges a written position statement setting
       forth the facts, legal theories, and proposed resolutions relevant to
       the dispute. The position statements shall be exchanged simultaneously
       to avoid any strategic advantage arising from sequential disclosure;

   (c) EXECUTIVE ESCALATION. If structured negotiation fails to resolve the
       dispute, the dispute shall be escalated to a senior executive of each
       party who has authority to bind the party and who has not previously
       been involved in the dispute. The senior executives shall meet (in
       person or by video conference) within ten (10) business days of
       escalation and shall negotiate in good faith for a period of not less
       than fifteen (15) business days;

   (d) MEDIATION. If executive escalation fails to resolve the dispute, the
       parties shall submit the dispute to non-binding mediation administered
       by a mutually agreed-upon mediation service. The mediator shall be
       selected by mutual agreement, or, failing agreement, by the mediation
       service. The costs of mediation shall be shared equally by the parties;
       and

   (e) CODE REVIEW. If mediation fails to resolve the dispute, and if the
       dispute relates to the technical interpretation or implementation of
       the Software, the parties may jointly submit the dispute to a panel of
       three (3) independent software engineers for a non-binding technical
       assessment. The panel members shall be selected by mutual agreement
       and shall each possess at least five (5) years of professional
       experience in at least two (2) of the following: Python, Perl, Rust,
       C, or the particular brand of architectural hubris exemplified by the
       Software.

Section 16.02. PRESERVATION OF RIGHTS. The pursuit of dispute resolution
through the escalation ladder set forth in Section 16.01 shall not prejudice,
waive, or otherwise affect either party's right to seek injunctive relief,
specific performance, or any other equitable remedy from a court of competent
jurisdiction at any time, if such relief is necessary to prevent irreparable
harm. The parties agree that deployment of the Software in a Production
environment would constitute irreparable harm for which monetary damages
would be inadequate.

Section 16.03. SEVERABILITY OF THIS ARTICLE. This Article XVI is included for
the purpose of establishing procedures for dispute resolution. Given the
nature of the Software and the likelihood that any dispute would center on
the question "why did you use this in production," the practical utility of
this Article may be limited. If this entire Article is deemed invalid, illegal,
unenforceable, unnecessarily elaborate, or indicative of an unhealthy
preoccupation with process, it may be severed from this Agreement without
affecting the validity or enforceability of any other provision.

