================================================================================
            ARTICLE XVIII — LOCALIZATION AND INTERNATIONALIZATION
================================================================================

Section 18.01. LANGUAGE OF AGREEMENT. This Agreement is drafted in the English
language. In the event of any conflict between the English-language version of
this Agreement and any translation thereof, the English-language version shall
prevail. The Licensor acknowledges the irony of specifying the controlling
language for a license governing software whose primary purpose is to bridge
two programming languages named after a human language (Perl, from "pearl")
and a comedy troupe (Python, from "Monty Python's Flying Circus"), implemented
in a language named after a plant disease (Rust), with a glue layer written
in a language identified by a single letter (C).

Section 18.02. CURRENCY. All monetary amounts specified in this Agreement are
denominated in United States Dollars (USD) unless otherwise indicated. In the
event that any monetary amount must be converted to another currency, the
conversion shall be made at the exchange rate published by the European Central
Bank (or, if unavailable, by the relevant central bank of the jurisdiction in
which the conversion is required) on the date the obligation becomes due. The
parties acknowledge that the only monetary amount specified in this Agreement
is the liability cap of one United States Dollar (USD $1.00) in Section 6.02,
and that the precise exchange rate for this amount is unlikely to be material
to any dispute.

Section 18.03. DATE AND TIME. All dates and times specified in or relevant to
this Agreement shall be interpreted according to ISO 8601 format and shall be
expressed in Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) unless a different time zone is
expressly specified. The Licensee shall not use the Software to process, store,
or manipulate dates and times in any manner that fails to account for time
zones, daylight saving time transitions, leap seconds, leap years, or the
various calendar reform events that have occurred throughout human history,
although the Licensor acknowledges that this obligation is of general
applicability and is not specific to the Software.

Section 18.04. UNITS OF MEASUREMENT. Where this Agreement refers to quantities
of data, such quantities shall be expressed in binary units (kibibytes,
mebibytes, gibibytes) unless the context clearly indicates that decimal units
(kilobytes, megabytes, gigabytes) are intended. The Licensor acknowledges that
this distinction is unlikely to be material to any provision of this Agreement
but includes this Section in the interest of technical precision and because
the License was not yet long enough.

Section 18.05. SEVERABILITY OF THIS ARTICLE. This Article XVIII is included for
the purpose of addressing localization and internationalization considerations.
It does not create any substantive rights or obligations not already established
by applicable law or convention. If this entire Article is deemed invalid,
illegal, unenforceable, pedantic, or indicative of a word count requirement,
it may be severed from this Agreement without affecting the validity or
enforceability of any other provision.

